secre00flem_0}}\n*{{cite book|last=Flexner|first=James Thomas|authorlink=James Thomas Flexner|title=George Washington in the American Revolution (1775\u20131783)|url=https://archive.org/details/georgewashington00flex|url-access=registration|location=Boston|publisher=Little, Brown|year=1968|oclc=166632872}} Second volume of Flexner's four-volume biography.\n*{{cite book|last=Flexner|first=James Thomas|title=Washington: The Indispensable Man|url=https://archive.org/details/washington00jame|url-access=registration|year=1974|publisher=Little, Brown|location=Boston, MA|oclc=450725539}} Single-volume condensation of Flexner's four-volume biography.\n*{{cite book|last=Freeman|first=Douglas S|authorlink=Douglas S. Freeman|title=George Washington: A Biography|url=https://archive.org/details/georgewashington0001free|url-access=registration|year=1948\u20131957|location=New York|publisher=Scribner|oclc=425613}} Seven volume scholarly biography, winner of the Pulitzer Prize.  Volumes 3\u20135 cover the Revolutionary War period.\n*{{cite book|last=Freeman|first=Douglas S|author2=Harwell, Richard |title=Washington|url=https://archive.org/details/washington00free|url-access=registration|year=1968|location=New York|publisher=Scribner|oclc=426557}} Abridgement of Freeman's multivolume biography.\n*{{Cite book|last=Furneaux|first=Rupert|title=The Battle of Saratoga|location=New York|publisher=Stein and Day|ref=Furneaux|year=1971|isbn=978-0-8128-1305-0|oclc=134959}}\n*{{cite book|last=Grizzard|first=Frank E., Jr|authorlink=Frank E. Grizzard, Jr.|title=George! A Guide to All Things Washington|location=Buena Vista and Charlottesville, VA|publisher=Mariner Publishing|year=2005|isbn=978-0-9768238-0-3|oclc=232006080}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Gruber|first=Ira|title=The Howe Brothers and the American Revolution|publisher=Atheneum Press|location=New York|year=1972|oclc=1464455|isbn=978-0-8078-1229-7}}\n*{{cite book|last=Higginbotham|first=Don|authorlink=Don Higginbotham|title=George Washington and 