\u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Aranga, Father: Smoko.\n#'''Porowhita''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Marama, Father: Takitimu.\n#'''P\u014dtonga''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Evohe, father: Te Kingi.\n#'''Quill''' - hatched 2019; mother: Kuia, father: Tamahou.\n#'''Rahotu''' - hatched 2019; mother: Nora, father: Sinbad (by Artificial Insemination).\n#'''Ralph''' \u2013 first captured: 1987 (Encounter with [[Douglas Adams]] and [[Mark Carwardine]] described in ''[[Last Chance to See]]''), (Likely the father of Merty).\n#'''Ranger''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Hinemoa, father: Horton.\n#'''Rangi''' \u2013 first captured: 1987; father of Zephyr '81 (Rediscovered February 2009, after hiding for 21 years on Codfish Island)<ref name=\"KRP 2009-02-08\" /> (likely also the father of Sarah and Wendy).\n#'''Robbie''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Heather, father: Sass.\n#'''Ruapuke''' \u2013 hatched: 2014; mother: Lisa, father: Blades (Formerly known as Lisa One; egg was crushed and repaired during incubation period.).\n#'''Ruggedy''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother Sue, father Blades.\n#'''Sage''' - Hatched: 2019; mother: Aparima, father: Basil.\n#'''Scotty''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Queenie, father: Tutoko.\n#'''Scratch''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Flossie, father: Whiskas.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Sinbad''' \u2013 hatched: 1998; mother: Flossie, father: Richard Henry; father of: Rahotu (by artificial insemination) '19. He is semi-imprinted, and likes to seek out human company. Andrew Digby via Twitter, 10 October 2018.\n#'''[[Sirocco (parrot)|Sirocco]]''' \u2013 hatched: 1997; mother: Zephyr, father: Felix (Unlikely to be used to breed. Encounter with [[Stephen Fry]] and [[Mark Carwardine]] described in ''[[Last Chance to See (TV series)|Last Chance to See]]'').\n#'''Stumpy''' \u2013 hatched: 1991; mother: John-girl, father: Pegasus; father of Jemma (by artificial insemination), Juanma (by artificial insemination) '09.\n#'''Tautahi''' - hatches: 2019; mother: Rakiura, father: Komaru.\n#'''Taeatanga''' \u2013 hatched: 2014; mother: Rakiura.\n#'''Takitimu''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Sue, father: Basil; father of Te Here, Tuterangi, Titapu \u201816; T\u014dmua, T\u016bmanako, \u014ctepoti, Kewa, Rere, Hikoi, Porowhita, T\u016bt\u0101nekai \u201819.\n#'''Tamahou''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Rakiura, father: Whiskas; father of Acheron, Deans, Hau, Mackenzie, Marangai, Quill \u201819.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Tau Kuhurangi''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Tumeke, father Boss\n#'''Te Atapo''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Rakiura, father: Whiskas; father of Bravo, Hanariki, Tut\u016b, Uri \u201819.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Te Awa''' \u2013 hatched: 2014; mother: Rakiura.\n#'''Te Here''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Hine Taumai, father: Takitimu.\n#'''Te Kingi''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Jean, father: Sass; father of Atat\u016b, Kohengi, Manaaki, Manawanui, Orion, P\u014dtonga, Whaea Jane \u201819.\n#'''Tiwai''' \u2013 hatched: 1997; mother: Zephyr, father: Felix.\n#'''T\u014dmua''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Tiwhiri, father: Takitimu.\n#'''Trevor''' \u2013 hatched: 1999; mother: Zephyr, father: Felix.\n#'''T\u016bmanako''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Tiwhiri, father Takitimu.\n#'''T\u016bt\u0101nekai''' - hatched: 2019, mother: Marama, father: Takitimu.\n#'''Tuterangi''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Hine Taumai, father: Takitimu.\n#'''Tutoko''' \u2013 hatched: 2011; mother: Rakiura, father: Barnard; father of Gale, K\u014draki, Koru, Scotty, Alison \u201819.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Uri''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Pura, father: Te Atapo.\n#'''Waihopai''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Kuihi, father: Barnard.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Whakakini''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Hinemoa, Father: Horton.\n#'''Wiremu''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Flossie, father: Whiskas.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Wolf''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Hananui, father: Merty.<ref name=nestlist/>\n\n==Fundraising==\nTo raise money for research, the New Zealand government's Department of Conservation operates a k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d adoption scheme. Adoptions are not exclusive; multiple people can adopt the same bird. Adoption is symbolic \u2013 k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d are a ''[[taonga]]'' (treasured) species, so no one can 'own' one. Adoption supports funding for k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d health management, supplementary food and annual transmitter changes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.doc.govt.nz/our-work/kakapo-recovery/get-involved/adopt-a-kakapo/|title=adopt-a-kakapo |date=}}</ref>\n\n==Recently deceased==\n''Names marked ''\u2021'' are of birds missing, presumed dead''\n\n===Females===\n*'''Mike'''\u2021 \u2013 Found in April 1982 on [[Stewart Island]] by Gary Aburn and the dog Mandy, transferred to [[Little Barrier Island]] a month later, the transmitter failed in 1982 and has been missing since then. (Possibly seen in 2015, there was a search in May 2018, but they haven't found anything yet).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/takapodigs/status/996872118758342656|title=Dr Andrew Digby on Twitter|website=Twitter|access-date=2018-05-16}}</ref>\n*'''John-Girl''' \u2013 mother of Stumpy '91; died: September 1991\n*'''Aroha''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Sue; died: July 2004<ref name=\"illness\"/>\n*'''Aurora''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Zephyr; died: July 2004<ref name=\"illness\"/>\n*'''Vollie''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Ruth; died: July 2004<ref name=\"illness\"/>\n*'''Mokopuna''' \u2013 hatched 2008; mother: Rakiura, father: Ox; died: 2008\n*'''Sarah''' \u2013 mother of Ariki '02; Pounamu '05; Paddy '09; died: May 2010<ref>[http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?view=article&id=232%3Afirst-adult-female-death-in-19-years&option=com_content&Itemid=435 First adult female death in 19 years ]</ref>\n*'''Purity''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Lisa, father: Basil; died: September 2011<ref name=nestlist/>\n*'''Monoa''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Margaret-Maree, father: Nog; died: September 2011\n*'''Sandra''' \u2013 mother of Morehu '99; died January 2012\n*'''Fuchsia''' \u2013 first captured: 1991; mother of Konini '02; Bluster-Murphy '09; died: March 2013\n*'''Taonga''' \u2013 hatched: 2011; mother: Rakiura, father: Barnard; died: April 2014<ref name=\"recoveryprogrammefront\"/>\n*'''Maggie''' \u2013 first captured: March 1980; died: May 2014, in a landslide (the second female captured on Stewart Island)\n*'''Ellie''' \u2013 hatched: 1999; mother: Lisa, father: Ox; died: July 2015 <ref>[http://kakaporecovery.org.nz/media-release-kakapo-ellie-found-dead-on-whenua-houcodfish-island/ Kakapo Ellie found dead on Whenua Hou/Codfish Island]</ref>\n*'''Wharetutu''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Hananui, father: Merty[16], died 2016\n*'''Jane''' - first captured 1989, found dead on Anchor Island, 18 August 2018 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/takapodigs/status/1030296548242948096}}</ref>\n*'''Hoki''' - hatched: 1992; mother: Zephyr, father: Felix (the first hand raised bird; subject of a book by her caretaker), died. 21 April 2019 from Aspergillosis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/takapodigs/status/1120244816711827456}}</ref>\n*'''Huhana''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Esperance, father: Whiskas; mother of Moorhouse '14, Huhu \u201819 (Youngest breeding female ever with 5 years)[18], died 23 May 2019 from Aspergillosis.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://twitter.com/takapodigs/status/1131808278038499328}}</ref>\n\n===Males===\n*'''Adler'''\u2021 \u2013 missing on Stewart island since 1981 (presumed killed by cats): hatched 1981; mother Nora, father Rangi\n*'''Tawbert'''\u2021 - missing in the Transit Valley since 1987, one of three [[Fiordland]] males known to have survived until then. May still be alive as booming was heard in the Transit in 2012.\n*'''Biscuit''' \u2021 - missing presumed dead, one of three Fiordland males known to have survived until 1987. (Discovered on the Tutoko high bench in Fiordland in 1984). \n*'''Snark'''\u2021 \u2013 missing on Little Barrier Island since 1990: hatched 1981; mother Alice, father Buster\n*'''Gunter'''\u2021 \u2013 missing on Codfish Island since 1987. (Found on Stewart Island in October 1981).\n*'''Pierre'''\u2021 \u2013 missing on [[Codfish Island]] since 1988\n*'''Tramp'''\u2021 \u2013 missing on Codfish Island since 1988<ref>Allison Ballance:\"Kakapo. Rescued from the brink of extinction\", Nelson 2010</ref>\n*'''Al'''\u2021 \u2013 missing on Codfish Island since 2010: hatched: 2002; mother: Alice, father: Waynebo\n*'''Gerry''' \u2013 died: 1991\n*'''Pegasus''' \u2013 father of Stumpy '91; died: 1993\n*'''Rob''' \u2013 died: February 1994 \n*'''Ken''' \u2013 first captured: 1988; died: July 1998 (transmitter harness injury)\n*'''Gunner''' \u2013 died: winter 2005\n*'''Bill''' \u2013 first captured: 1982; father of Dobbie '91; Esperance, Horton, Rakiura '02; Pura, Yasmine '05; JEM '08; died: March 2008<ref name=\"KRP 2008-04-01\"/>\n*'''Lee''' \u2013 died: 28 October 2008<ref name=\"KRP 2008-11-11\"/>\n*'''Sass''' \u2013 father of Robbie, Palmersan, Te Kingi, Blake, Kuihi '02; Kumi '05; died: February 2010<ref name=KRP>[http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?view=article&id=224:old-boy-sass-farewelled&option=com_content&Itemid=435 Old boy Sass farewelled.] Retrieved 29 June 2010</ref> \n*'''Richard Henry''' \u2013 first captured: 1975; father of Gulliver, Kuia, Sinbad '98; found dead: 24 December 2010<ref>William Stolzenburg. ''Rat Island'', 2011. See \"Acknowledgements\".</ref><ref>[http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?view=article&id=242%3Akakapo-males-boom-on-as-legendary-bird-dies&option=com_content&Itemid=221 Kakapo males \u2018boom\u2019 on as legendary bird dies] Retrieved January 13th 2011</ref> (The last bird from the [[South Island]], he was captured by [[Don Merton]], John Cheyne, and Mandy dog in 1975 in [[Fiordland National Park]]/Gulliver Valley/Esperance River, named after [[Richard Treacy Henry]])\n*'''Whiskas''' \u2013 first captured: 1989; father of Tamahou, Tiaho, Te Atapo, Wiremu, Huhana, Scratch '09; died: January 2011\n*'''Waynebo''' \u2013 father of Ariki, Konini, Pearl, Al, Tumeke, Hine taumai, Aparima '02; Pounamu '05; Ihi, Komaru, Stella '11; died: January 2012<ref name=nestlist/>\n*'''Rooster''' \u2013 hatched: 2008; mother: Sue, father: Basil; died: March 2012<ref name=\"KRP 2008-11-11\"/>\n*'''Barnard''' \u2013 first captured: 1982; father of Awarua, Waihopai, Hokonui '09; Hakatere, Taonga, Tia, Tutoko, Waa '11; died: April 2012<ref name=nestlist/>\n*'''Ben''' \u2013 father of Heather '81; died: April 2014\n*'''Lionel''' \u2013 first captured: 1981 (likely was a juvenile at the time); died: June 2014\n*'''Smoko''' \u2013 first captured: 1991; father of Bluster, Ra (by artificial insemination) '09; Clout, Percy '16; died: February 2016<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.radionz.co.nz/news/national/296983/first-kakapo-of-the-year-safely-hatched |title = First kakapo of the year safely hatched|date = 2016-02-19}}</ref>\n*'''Tiaho''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Rakiura, father: Whiskas<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/takapodigs/status/707681904586133504|title=Dr Andrew Digby on Twitter|website=Twitter|access-date=2016-03-09}}</ref> : died March 2016 from fight.\n*'''Blake''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Jean, father: Sass; father of Hugh, Mukeke, Ninihi, Kokoto, Aumaria, Gertrude '16 Died: December 2017 from heat stress. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.odt.co.nz/regions/southland/endangered-fiordland-kakapo-dies-heat-stress|title=Endangered Fiordland kakapo dies from heat stress|date=2017-12-05|website=Otago Daily Times Online News|language=en|access-date=2019-07-16}}</ref>\n*'''Jimmy''' - Died: December 2017 from complications following an anesthetic procedure.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://kakaporecovery.org.nz/blog/2017/12/20/population-falls-151/ | title=K\u0101k\u0101p\u014d Recovery}}</ref>\n*'''Kotiu''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother Nora, father Blades - Died: February 2018\n*'''Dobbie''' \u2013 hatched: 1991; mother: Wendy, father: Bill; father of Mahli, Tohu '14 - Died: 12 March 2018 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/KakapoRecovery/photos/a.182258705165224.45401.179503412107420/1728252833899129/|title=K\u0101k\u0101p\u014d Recovery|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-22}}</ref>\n*'''Piripi''' - caught in January 1990. Died ca. 3 January 2019 of injuries consistent with fighting, possibly inflicted by Ng\u0101tapa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/KakapoRecovery/photos/a.182258705165224/2108479619209780/?type=3&theater|title=Anchor Update!|website=www.facebook.com|access-date=2019-01-03|date=2019-01-03}}</ref>\n*'''Arab''' - first captured by Gary \u2018Arab\u2019 Aburn <ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.doc.govt.nz/2015/10/12/gary-aburn-saving-the-kakapo/|title=The remarkable hunter that helped save the k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d|date=2015-10-11}}</ref> in 1980; father of Egilsay, Hera '16, Died 2 May 2019 from complications relating to an eye injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/takapodigs/status/1123725338968772610}}</ref>\n*'''Gumboots''' - first captured: 1988, died 3 May 2019 after getting his leg trapped in a forked branch on Whenua Hou and not being able to free himself.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/takapodigs/status/1124844843895742464}}</ref>\n*'''Merty''' - Hatched: unknown; mother: Lisa, father: Ralph; father of Wolf, Moss, Millie, Wharetutu \u201809. Declared dead. 21 May 2019, not seen for 5 years<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/business/112894004/five-endangered-kkp-die-in-month-from-fungal-disease|title=Fungal disease is killing New Zealand's rare k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d}}</ref>\n*'''Felix''' \u2013 first captured: 1989; father of Hoki, Tiwai, Sirocco, Manu '97; Boomer, Morehu, Trevor '99; Maestro, Evohe '09, Attenborough, Punga, Faulkner '16. Died September 2019 on Little Barrier Island<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/KakapoRecovery/?hc_ref=ARTB6WRQfCLb0n3-MU7wVmfTUvClVRedjKnhV8AINKLEJnnh36m8xv0C1ZlBX6JJk0I&fref=nf&__xts__[0]=68.ARB_0xMfrIxTkj1Dj7qqu7uTsbgDg7EFxhsH-o-3bHrRG852kSYj85wf0z-oKfZnqEjpK4P27We34PvBvUib9Q_1tbnemPaBRJ2tgtBmXjbaLK43gKKy0GmmpYJ19S8NwfWmO5-0mA6b4-3p71qsnx2QfiSSVwJgPgaq4_IL5zEQmxsO-V5WgrvkHhN1XCpGa2p7o5ezeXGyHFVx95_Zpu_3zV8iNWTS8E8gcBWfJe6gZ0bPBwfdKx7rD6pFAOFI03oqsauVwlCcUVBPdfDBKLZ9xXteH4U1ylSdfOsvO8lOAHLGJ358238-eAko1HiPhO-mewoiWJBq9eJttC0f-DWuXg&__tn__=kC-R}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n<!-- This link: http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=137&Itemid=235 has been added to the automatic references. See number 11 on the list. -->\n\n==Further reading==\n*Ballance, Alison: \"Kakapo. Rescued from the brink of extinction\", Appendix 1, Kakapo names, page 242\u2013265, alphabetical list of all known 233 adult Kakapo, with a short info on each bird (alive or dead). Potton & Burton, Nelson 09/2018, 276 pages. {{ISBN|9781877517273}}. https://www.pottonandburton.co.nz/store/kakapo-2018\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.doc.govt.nz/kakapo-recovery Kakapo Recovery Programme]\n\n{{Strigopidae}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kakapo}}\n[[Category:Lists of birds]]\n[[Category:Critically endangered animals]]\n[[Category:Birds of New Zealand|']]\n[[Category:Strigopidae]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:Strigops habroptilus 1.jpg|thumb|right|Female k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d Pura on [[Codfish Island]]]]\nEvery known living '''[[kakapo|k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d]]''', except some young chicks, has been given a name by [[Kakapo Recovery Programme|K\u0101k\u0101p\u014d Recovery Programme]] officials. Many of the older birds were given [[English language]] names, but more recent chicks have been given [[M\u0101ori language|M\u0101ori]] names. Some k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d, such as Richard Henry and Moorhouse, are named after people who have provided assistance to the preservation efforts. A k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d interactive family tree is available.<ref>{{cite web |title=The K\u0101k\u0101p\u014d |url=https://public.tableau.com/views/TheKakapo/Dashboard1?:embed=y&:display_count=yes&:toolbar=no&:showVizHome=no}}</ref>\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==Recent population changes==\nAfter a good breeding year in 2002, the population remained at 86 until 2004, when three two-year-old female k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d died from infections by the soil bacterium ''[[Erysipelas]]''.<ref name=\"illness\">{{cite press release|title=Kakapo illness identified |url=http://www.biodiversity.govt.nz/news/media/current/13jul04.html |date=13 July 2004 |publisher=Biodiversity Information Online, New Zealand Government |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081014070022/http://www.biodiversity.govt.nz/news/media/current/13jul04.html | archivedate = 14 October 2008 | url-status = dead }}</ref><ref name=\"Gartrell\">B. D. Gartrell; M. R. Alley; H. Mack; J. Donald; K. McInnes; and P. Jansen (2005). Erysipelas in the critically endangered kakapo (Strigops habroptilus). ''Avian Pathology'', 34 (5), 383\u2013387. {{doi|10.1080/03079450500268583}}.</ref> Four chicks survived from the 2005 breeding season. The male Gunner died of [[aflatoxicosis]] during the New Zealand winter of 2005, bringing the population back to 86.<ref>Merton, D. (2005). [http://www.parrots.org/pdfs/our_publications/psittascene/2005/05May63.pdf Kakapo update 2005]. ''PsittaScene'', 17 (2), 7\u20139.</ref> In April 2008, the population grew to 93<ref>{{cite web|title=World kakapo population rises by five|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/section/1/story.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10501192|date=31 March 2008|work=NZ Herald|accessdate=2008-03-31}}</ref> with the hatching of seven chicks,<ref name=\"KRP 2008-04-08\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=158:all-eggs-hatched&catid=53:ranger-diaries&Itemid=207 |title=Ranger's Diaries: All eggs hatched |publisher=Kakapo Recovery Programme |date=2008-04-08 |accessdate=2008-04-12}}</ref> then fell to 92 due to the death of adult Bill.<ref name=\"KRP 2008-04-01\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=155:more-chicks&catid=53:ranger-diaries&Itemid=207 |title=Ranger's Diaries: More chicks, but we've lost our friend Bill |publisher=Kakapo Recovery Progr04-01 |accessdate=2008-04-12}}</ref> One of the seven 2008 chicks died soon after hatching,<ref name=\"KRP 2008-03-24\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=153:sadness-at-easter&catid=53:ranger-diaries&Itemid=207 |title=Ranger's Diaries: Sadness at Easter |publisher=Kakapo Recovery Programme |date=2008-03-24 |accessdate=2008-04-12}}</ref> bringing the total down to 91, and on 28 October 2008, male Lee died, bringing the population down to 90.<ref name=\"KRP 2008-11-11\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=172:ranger-diaries&catid=53:ranger-diaries&Itemid=207 |title=Spring has sprung! |publisher=Kakapo Recovery Programme |date=2008-11-11 |accessdate=2008-11-15}}</ref> Male Rangi was rediscovered in February 2009 after spending 21 years living on Codfish Island.<ref name=\"KRP 2009-02-08\">{{cite news |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/4841375a11.html |title=Kakapo back to nest after 21 years |author=Mussen, Deidre |date=5 March 2009 |work=[[The Sunday Star-Times]] |accessdate=15 October 2011}}</ref> The 2009 breeding season resulted in 33 chicks (20 male and 13 female), bringing the population up to 124.<ref name=\"124 Kakapo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/southland-times/news/2416123/Another-chance-to-see-kakapo|title=Another chance to see kakapo |author=AMY MILNE|publisher=The Southland Times|date=2009-05-16}}</ref> A number of older birds died during 2010, followed by the significant loss of the only remaining [[Fiordland]] k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d, Richard Henry, announced during January 2011. His Fiordland genes survive through his three progeny.<ref name=\"richardhenry2010\">{{cite web|last=DOC|first=Media release|title=K\u0101k\u0101p\u014d males 'boom' on as legendary bird dies|url=http://www.doc.govt.nz/about-doc/news/media-releases/2011/kakapo-males-boom-on-as-legendary-bird-dies/|publisher=NZ Department of Conservation}}</ref>\nThe breeding season in 2011 produced 11 chicks (eight females, three male), which all survived, bringing the population to 131. However, the deaths of several birds followed and with no breeding season in 2012, the population dropped to 124.<ref name=\"recoveryprogrammefront\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/ |title=Home of the Kakapo Recovery Programme &#124; Kakapo Recovery Programme |publisher=Kakaporecovery.org.nz |date= |accessdate=2012-07-12}}</ref> As of May 2014, with the hatching of six eggs (the first hatchings since 2011) the total population had increased to 130 living individuals.\n\nForty-seven chicks hatched in the 2016 nesting season, making it a \"record breeding season\". As of July 2016, 34 of them had survived.<ref name=\"hatchingseason2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.beehive.govt.nz/release/final-kakapo-egg-year-hatches |title=Final Kakpo egg of the year hatches |publisher=Kakaporecovery.org.nz |date= |accessdate=2016-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=takapodigs|author=Dr Andrew Digby|number=741787234110574593|date=12 June 2016|title=Another blow. #kakapo chick Zephyr2, 60d, has died. She was ill with respiratory condition and undergoing treatment.}}</ref>\n\nAs of January 2020, the New Zealand Dept of Conservation site showed a population of {{Number of Living Kakapo}}.\n\n== Living k\u0101k\u0101p\u014d ({{Number of Living Kakapo}}<!-- to update this number see link on the talk page -->) ==\n\n===Females (99)===\n[[File:Kakapo-population-size.svg|thumb|400px|Kakapo population development]]\n#'''Adelaide''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Kuia, father: Kumi.\n#'''\u1fb9io''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Mila, father: Horton.\n#'''Ako''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Esperance, father: Komaru.\n#'''Alice''' \u2013 first captured: 1981; mother of Snark '81, Manu '97; Al, Pearl '02, Huarangi, Vori, Whet\u016b \u201819.\n#'''Alison''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Queenie, father: Tutoko.\n#'''Aparima''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Wendy, father: Waynebo; mother of JEM '08, Bunker, Chicory, Sage, Horopito \u201819.\n#'''Aranga''' \u2013 hatched: 1999; mother: Lisa, father: Ox;{{cn|date=January 2017}} mother of Jack '09, Waikawa '11, Percy, Clout '16.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''\u0100ria''' \u2013 hatched: 2019; mother: Awarua, father: Komaru.\n#'''Atareta''' \u2013 hatched: 2011; mother: Lisa, father: Blades; mother of Manaaki, Atatu, Whaea Jane \u201819.\n#'''Atat\u016b''' - hatched 2019; mother: Atareta, father: Te Kingi.\n#'''Aumaria''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Stella, father: Blake.<ref name=\"blake\"/>\n#'''Awarua''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Kuihi, father: Barnard; mother of Motup\u014dhue, \u0100ria, Matariki '19.<ref name=nestlist>{{cite web|url=http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=137&Itemid=235| title=Kakapo Nesting Table|access-date=29 June 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100604224131/http://www.kakaporecovery.org.nz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=137&Itemid=235|archive-date=4 June 2010}}</ref>\n#'''Bella''' \u2013 first captured: 1982; mother of Tiaka, Hillary, Roha '09, Verity \u201819.\n#'''Boomer''' \u2013 hatched: 1999; mother: Zephyr, father: Felix; mother of  Deans, Hau, Marangai \u201819.\n#'''Cyndy''' \u2013 first captured: 1987; mother of Horton '02; Weheruatanga-o-te-po, Elwin, Jester '08; Ngatapa, Queenie '09.\n#'''Dusky''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Tiwhiri, father: Horton.\n#'''Elsie''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Waikawa, father: Horton.\n#'''Esperance''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Flossie, father: Bill; mother of Huhana '09, Ako, Matakana, Toiroa \u201819.\n#'''Eva ''' - hatched: 2019 - mother: Suzanne, father: Gulliver.\n#'''Evohe''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Zephyr, father: Felix; mother of P\u014dtonga, K\u014dhengi \u201819.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Flossie''' \u2013 first captured: by 1982; mother of Heather '81; Kuia, Gulliver, Sinbad '98; Rakiura, Esperance '02; Yasmine, Pura '05; Wiremu, Scratch '09; Hakatere, Waa '11.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Galaxy''' - hatched: 2019; Mother: Ihi, father Guapo.\n#'''Gale''' - hatched: 2019; Mother: Nora, father Tutoko.\n#'''Gertrude''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Kuia, father: Blake.<ref name=\"blake\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/takapodigs/status/1005227125497004032|title=We've finally (!) got #genetic paternity results for 2016 #kakapo chicks|date=8 June 2018|access-date=8 January 2019}}</ref>\n#'''Hakatere''' \u2013 hatched: 2011; mother: Flossie, father: Barnard.<ref name=\"recoveryprogrammefront\"/>\n#'''Hananui''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Lisa, father: Blades; mother of Wharetutu, Wolf '09.\n#'''Hanariki''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Pura, father: Te Atapo.\n#'''Hau''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Boomer, father: Tamahou.\n#'''Hauturu''' \u2013 hatched: 1999; mother: Lisa, father: Ox.\n#'''Heather''' \u2013 hatched: 1981; mother: Flossie, father: Ben; mother of Palmersan, Robbie '02; Guapo, Awhero '09; Mahli, Tohu '14.\n#'''Hera''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother Suzanne, father Arab.\n#'''Hinemoa''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Sue, father: Basil; mother of Ranger, Whakakini \u201819. <ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''Hine taumai''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Wendy, father: Waynebo; mother of Te Here, Tuterangi, Titapu '16.\n#'''Huarangi''' - hatched: 2019, mother: Alice, father: Boss.\n#'''Huh\u016b''' - Hatched: 2019; mother: Huhana, father: Guapo.\n#'''Ihi''' \u2013 hatched: 2011; mother: Solstice, father: Waynebo<ref name=\"recoveryprogrammefront\"/>; mother of: Galaxy, Hondy '19.\n#'''Jean''' \u2013 first captured: 1981; mother of Blake, Kuihi, Te Kingi '02.\n#'''JEM''' \u2013 hatched: 2008; mother: Aparima, father: Bill.<ref name=\"KRP 2008-11-11\"/>\n#'''Jemma''' \u2013 hatched: 2009; mother: Pearl, father: Stumpy (by artificial insemination); mother of Lind \u201819.<ref name=nestlist/>\n#'''K\u014dhengi''' - hatched: 2019, mother: Evohe, father: Te Kingi.\n#'''Konini''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Fuchsia, father: Waynebo; mother of Hugh '16.\n#'''Koru''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Kuihi, father: Tutoko.\n#'''Kuia''' \u2013 hatched: 1998; mother: Flossie, father: Richard Henry; mother of Gertrude, Marian, Adeliade, Henry '16, Acheron, Mackenzie, Quill '19.\n#'''Kuihi''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Jean, father: Sass; mother of Awarua, Waihopai, Hokonui '09, Oraka '16, Koru, M\u0101hutonga \u201819.\n#'''Kura''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Tumeke, father Boss.\n#'''Lisa''' \u2013 first captured: by August 1982; mother of Ellie, Hauturu, Aranga '99; Hananui '02; Tiwhiri, Hurihrui, Purity '09; Atareta '11; Ruapuke '14 (Presumed lost on Little Barrier Island for 13 years; rediscovered on a nest in 1999.)<ref name=nestlist/> (Encounter with [[Stephen Fry]] and [[Mark Carwardine]] described in ''[[Last Chance to See (TV series)#5. \"Kakapo\"|Last Chance to See]]''.) (Likely also the mother of Merty and Joe).\n#'''Madison''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Waikawa, father Horton.\n#'''Mahli''' \u2013 hatched: 2014; mother: Heather, father: Dobbie.\n#'''Makorea''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Waikawa, father Kumi.\n#'''Matariki'''  \u2013 hatched: 2019; mother: Awarua, father: Komaru.\n#'''Mati-M\u0101''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Rakiura, father: Komaru.\n#'''Marama''' \u2013 hatched: 2002; mother: Margaret-Maree, father: Nog; Mother of Hikoi, Porowhita, T\u016bt\u0101nekai \u201819.\n#'''Margaret-Maree''' \u2013 first captured: 1986; mother of Marama, Mila, Moana '02; Kumi '05; Millie, Moss '09 (Likely the mother of Sarah and Wendy).\n#'''Marian''' \u2013 hatched: 2016; mother: Kuia, father: Kumi.\n#'''Matakana''' - hatched: 2019; mother: Esperance, father Komaru.\n#'''Mila''' \u2013 